ZH: 农民每天早晨都会去浇灌田地。
EN: The farmers go to irrigate the fields every morning.

ZH: 这个花园需要定时浇灌。
EN: This garden needs to be watered regularly.

ZH: 我们应该在傍晚浇灌植物。
EN: We should water the plants in the evening.

ZH: 她喜欢浇灌花草并观察它们的成长。
EN: She enjoys watering plants and watching them grow.

ZH: 春雨沐浴着这片土地，也给它浇灌了生命。
EN: The spring rain bathes the land and gives it life.

ZH: 他们用灌溉系统来自动浇灌庄稼。
EN: They use an irrigation system to automatically water the crops.

ZH: 花园的浇灌务必坚持，方能长青。
EN: The watering of the garden must be adhered to in order to stay evergreen.

ZH: 不要浪费水资源，我们应该节约使用浇灌的水。
EN: Don't waste water resources, we should save the water used for irrigation.

ZH: 这台浇灌设备每次可以喷洒很大的面积。
EN: This irrigation equipment can spray a large area each time.

ZH: 他负责浇灌果园里的各种水果树。
EN: He is responsible for watering the various fruit trees in the orchard.

ZH: 为了确保庄稼茁壮成长，必须定期浇灌。
EN: In order to ensure the healthy growth of crops, they must be watered regularly.

ZH: 这片土地不适合作庄稼，因为没有水源可以用来浇灌。
EN: This land is not suitable for crops because there is no water source for irrigation.

ZH: 在干旱的季节里，特别要注意浇灌。
EN: In dry seasons, special attention should be paid to irrigation.

ZH: 过犹不及，浇灌过多会导致植物腐烂。
EN: Excessive watering can cause plant rot, so be careful not to over-water.

ZH: 浇灌时要注意植物的根部是否受到影响。
EN: When watering, pay attention to whether the roots of the plant are affected.

ZH: 冬天的时候也需要适量的浇灌，以保持植物健康。
EN: Watering is also needed in winter to maintain the health of plants.

ZH: 雨季来临前，一定要加大浇灌力度。
EN: Before the rainy season arrives, increase the intensity of watering.

ZH: 使用节水浇灌系统可以有效减少用水量。
EN: The use of water-saving irrigation systems can effectively reduce water consumption.

ZH: 植物生长需要充足的阳光和适量的浇灌。
EN: Plant growth requires sufficient sunlight and adequate watering.
